      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum linear elastic model with nonlinear contact is appropriate for titanium alloy at loads below fracture; plasticity model activated above yield.",
      "rationale": "The FEA uses a bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity model for Ti-6Al-4V, consistent with the monotonic loading protocol of ASTM F1717. Contact between screw head and rod is modeled with augmented Lagrangian formulation. Model form is well-established for metallic implant structural analysis. Gradation 2 achieved."
