      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the clinical failure modes of construct loosening and screw fracture.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load transfer to adjacent vertebrae. Yield force and force at 40 mm displacement characterize the onset and extent of plastic deformation, which correlates with fatigue life and clinical fracture risk. QoIs are accepted surrogates for in vivo performance in ASTM F1717 regulatory submissions. Gradation 2 achieved."
