    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved Gradation 1 against a required Gradation 2 due to single test condition; this gap is acknowledged and accepted given the direct regulatory precedent for single-condition ASTM F1717 testing. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-specified acceptance bounds. The FEA modeling framework is accepted as credible for predicting compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
